Date: Thu 15 Oct 2015
Source: OIE, WAHID weekly disease information; 28(42) [summarized, edited] http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapFullEventReport&reportid=18871


Lumpy skin disease [LSD], Russia
--------------------------------
Information received on 15 Oct 2015 from Dr Evgeny Nepoklonov, Deputy Head, Federal Service for Veterinary and Phytosanitary Surveillance, Ministry of Agriculture, Moscow, Russia

Summary

Report type: Follow-up report No. 4
Date of start of the event: 7 Jul 2015
Date of confirmation of the event: 3 Sep 2015
Report date: 15 Oct 2015
Date submitted to OIE: 15 Oct 2015
Reason for notification: 1st occurrence of a listed disease
Manifestation of disease: Clinical disease
Causal agent: Lumpy skin disease virus
Nature of diagnosis: Clinical, Laboratory (basic), Laboratory (advanced), Necropsy
This event pertains to the whole country.

New outbreaks (3)
[For the statistics of each outbreak, please refer to the source URL. Of the 3 new outbreaks, 2 were reported from Dagestan, and one, which reportedly started on 25 Aug 2015, from the Republic of Chechnya. - Mod.AS]

Summary of outbreaks
Total [new] outbreaks: 3
Total animals affected
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 966 / 26 / 0 / 2 / -

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[According to OIE's archived summary, since the start of the LSD event in the southwest of the Russian Federation on 7 Jul 2015, a total of 13 outbreaks have been reported involving 2 republics, Dagestan and Chechnya.

Outbreak summary:
Total new outbreaks: 13 (submitted)
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 3391 / 88 / 3 / 10 / 0

